1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:00,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:31,966
Help! Help!

3
00:01:33,469 --> 00:01:35,095
- Loki, wake up.
- Rhea.

4
00:01:36,458 --> 00:01:37,876
What are you doing here?

5
00:01:39,881 --> 00:01:40,881
What?

6
00:01:41,555 --> 00:01:43,015
Just checking if I'm still alive?

7
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:12,519
You don’t have to
watch over me, Lorelei.

8
00:02:14,122 --> 00:02:15,540
I can take care of myself.

9
00:02:16,993 --> 00:02:20,538
It’s been days since I was discharged
from the hospital.

10
00:02:21,537 --> 00:02:25,874
The doctor said you should
avoid strenuous activities.

11
00:02:26,166 --> 00:02:30,212
So I’m just making sure
you don’t do anything reckless.

12
00:02:33,774 --> 00:02:37,152
Even if I wanted to,
I don’t have enough energy.

13
00:02:39,958 --> 00:02:43,712
But I've noticed a change
in your behavior.

14
00:02:45,323 --> 00:02:47,868
Did I miss something
while I was asleep at the hospital?

15
00:02:48,388 --> 00:02:49,973
Is there something I should know?

16
00:03:02,161 --> 00:03:03,287
Who are you?

17
00:03:03,597 --> 00:03:06,183
It’s not safe to be out this late
by yourself.

18
00:03:10,468 --> 00:03:11,468
Hey!

19
00:03:12,427 --> 00:03:13,761
Are you still with us?

20
00:03:14,407 --> 00:03:15,909
Yes. Sorry!

21
00:03:17,072 --> 00:03:20,242
You know, don’t overthink things for now.

22
00:03:20,437 --> 00:03:24,150
We’ll talk about our cases
once you’re better.

23
00:03:25,184 --> 00:03:26,185
Loki?

24
00:03:27,315 --> 00:03:28,358
Hi, Tita.

25
00:03:30,685 --> 00:03:33,396
How are you?
How are you feeling?

26
00:03:34,193 --> 00:03:35,193
Good.

27
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:40,115
I’d be better
if I wasn’t being watched 24/7.

28
00:03:43,677 --> 00:03:44,678
If that’s the case,

29
00:03:45,637 --> 00:03:46,638
here’s what I’ll do.

30
00:03:47,164 --> 00:03:48,832
I’ll lock your unit.

31
00:03:49,541 --> 00:03:51,501
Do whatever you want.

32
00:03:52,211 --> 00:03:53,897
You have your phone anyway, right?

33
00:03:53,921 --> 00:03:57,506
If you need anything,
just call us. Okay?

34
00:03:57,507 --> 00:03:59,110
- If you need anything, just call us. Okay?
- Wait.

35
00:03:59,134 --> 00:04:00,134
What?

36
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:11,284
Shadows

37
00:04:11,308 --> 00:04:14,019
in the dark are crawling

38
00:04:14,837 --> 00:04:18,633
Keeping watch and barring your way

39
00:04:18,658 --> 00:04:22,204
As if the line could not be crossed

40
00:04:23,030 --> 00:04:26,616
To every scream and every tremor

41
00:04:26,617 --> 00:04:29,786
These walls remain the only witness

42
00:04:29,787 --> 00:04:32,920
Every noise is etched in here

43
00:04:32,944 --> 00:04:37,448
Like fire and ammunition for your memory

44
00:04:38,752 --> 00:04:41,159
Heed the warnings

45
00:04:41,999 --> 00:04:44,632
The threats poised to strike

46
00:04:45,461 --> 00:04:49,775
For this world

47
00:04:49,799 --> 00:04:52,425
is not what you imagined

48
00:04:52,426 --> 00:04:54,887
Heed the warnings

49
00:04:55,888 --> 00:04:58,015
Open up your eyes

50
00:04:59,274 --> 00:05:02,819
For this world

51
00:05:03,562 --> 00:05:06,349
is not what you imagined

52
00:05:06,373 --> 00:05:11,211
Heed the warnings

53
00:05:15,549 --> 00:05:17,092
Good morning.

54
00:05:18,150 --> 00:05:19,819
Lori! Lori, wait!

55
00:05:19,844 --> 00:05:21,763
Oh, Rosetta. How are you?

56
00:05:23,191 --> 00:05:24,942
How’s Loki doing, by the way?

57
00:05:25,642 --> 00:05:27,184
Is he okay now?

58
00:05:27,185 --> 00:05:32,274
Well, he’s still recovering,
so it might be a while before he’s back.

59
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:34,125
Oh, I see.

60
00:05:35,097 --> 00:05:36,766
So, what about your club?

61
00:05:37,048 --> 00:05:40,260
Well, for now,
I’ll take care of the club.

62
00:05:41,976 --> 00:05:42,976
Why?

63
00:05:43,414 --> 00:05:45,374
Do you have a case for us?

64
00:05:46,182 --> 00:05:50,142
I do. My friend’s being
bothered by someone.

65
00:05:50,898 --> 00:05:54,944
But it’s okay.
Maybe when your partner gets back.

66
00:05:58,675 --> 00:06:01,737
- No offense meant, okay? Sorry.
- None taken.

67
00:06:01,747 --> 00:06:07,451
I mean, I know
I’m not as good as Loki at solving cases.

68
00:06:08,018 --> 00:06:09,977
It’s not like that.

69
00:06:09,978 --> 00:06:11,997
So you won’t have a hard time.

70
00:06:14,039 --> 00:06:15,165
Okay.

71
00:06:22,099 --> 00:06:23,359
Hey.

72
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:27,011
Our normal counting system
is called “base ten”

73
00:06:28,085 --> 00:06:33,049
because we have exactly ten symbols
to work with from zero to nine.

74
00:06:33,484 --> 00:06:37,696
But once we run out of these symbols,
we start all over again.

75
00:06:38,122 --> 00:06:40,501
We add another digit to the left.

76
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:43,236
That’s because we have ten fingers.

77
00:06:43,941 --> 00:06:46,235
But what if we had eight?

78
00:06:47,193 --> 00:06:52,031
We count using digits zero to seven,
then we go 10 to 17.

79
00:06:52,499 --> 00:06:57,545
Yes, and that is called
octal counting or base eight.

80
00:07:01,229 --> 00:07:03,690
Okay, class. Lunch break.

81
00:07:04,514 --> 00:07:05,849
See you next session.

82
00:07:08,001 --> 00:07:10,087
Could he really be M?

83
00:07:10,885 --> 00:07:13,304
It’s kind of hard to believe.

84
00:07:14,041 --> 00:07:16,544
He seems nice and innocent.

85
00:07:16,896 --> 00:07:20,942
Besides, if he was involved
in Stein Alberts’ kidnapping,

86
00:07:21,532 --> 00:07:24,118
why would he report it to the Q.E.D. Club?

87
00:07:24,777 --> 00:07:25,945
So, shall we go?

88
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:30,116
- Come on, I’m starving. Aren’t you hungry?
- Alright.

89
00:07:31,453 --> 00:07:33,429
Lori! Lori!

90
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:37,586
I hope you didn’t take
what I said earlier too personally.

91
00:07:37,610 --> 00:07:39,653
Not really. It’s okay.

92
00:07:41,588 --> 00:07:42,881
How about this?

93
00:07:43,405 --> 00:07:45,741
Let’s have lunch at the mall. My treat.

94
00:07:46,098 --> 00:07:49,059
Come on, please?

95
00:07:49,084 --> 00:07:50,878
- Hmm...
- I am hungry.

96
00:07:50,902 --> 00:07:52,195
Alright, fine.

97
00:07:53,408 --> 00:07:55,118
- Really?
- Oh, wait.

98
00:07:56,635 --> 00:07:59,677
I'm bored.
Check for clients in the club room.

99
00:07:59,701 --> 00:08:01,703
If interesting, send ASAP.

100
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:05,609
Sorry, Rosetta. Looks like
I have to eat lunch in the clubroom.

101
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:08,946
Loki asked me to come by
in case there are new cases.

102
00:08:08,970 --> 00:08:09,970
Huh?

103
00:08:10,623 --> 00:08:15,192
Why not just say you’re in the clubroom
when you’re really at the mall?

104
00:08:15,216 --> 00:08:17,712
Of course, you deserve a break too.

105
00:08:17,736 --> 00:08:21,366
But what if someone
really needs help?

106
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:24,601
You won’t be able to solve it
without Loki anyway, right?

107
00:08:25,899 --> 00:08:29,175
I mean, there are only
two of you in the club.

108
00:08:29,199 --> 00:08:32,071
So, it’ll be hard if
you’re there alone, right?

109
00:08:32,072 --> 00:08:33,823
So that makes it even harder...

110
00:08:34,594 --> 00:08:38,261
You know what?
I’m okay eating alone.

111
00:08:38,286 --> 00:08:40,330
So, go on.
Just head to the mall.

112
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:44,524
Lori! Wait!

113
00:08:52,624 --> 00:08:55,627
Are you okay being alone there?

114
00:08:57,454 --> 00:08:59,331
Anything interesting yet?

115
00:09:00,624 --> 00:09:01,750
Nothing yet.

116
00:09:02,621 --> 00:09:03,622
Come in!

117
00:09:06,805 --> 00:09:09,933
Hi! This is Q.E.D. Club, right?

118
00:09:10,832 --> 00:09:13,876
Yep, that’s right.
How can I help you?

119
00:09:14,564 --> 00:09:17,025
Wait, are you Lorelei Rios?

120
00:09:17,365 --> 00:09:21,202
The one who writes all the
blogs about Q.E.D. cases.

121
00:09:22,672 --> 00:09:23,766
And...

122
00:09:23,790 --> 00:09:25,875
is this the place where
every case starts?

123
00:09:26,353 --> 00:09:27,954
Yes, that’s right. It’s me.

124
00:09:27,961 --> 00:09:33,800
And, yes,
this is where students come for help.

125
00:09:35,242 --> 00:09:37,886
Sorry for not introducing myself
right away.

126
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:39,453
I’m Agatha Cortez, by the way.

127
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:41,915
The literary editor of the Clark Clarion.

128
00:09:41,939 --> 00:09:43,044
It’s nice to meet you.

129
00:09:43,057 --> 00:09:46,077
And I also read your blogs.

130
00:09:46,101 --> 00:09:47,337
Really?

131
00:09:47,361 --> 00:09:52,021
Wow, that's huge for a newbie writer
like me to be praised

132
00:09:52,029 --> 00:09:56,431
by an editor from Clark University's
official publication like you.

133
00:09:57,090 --> 00:09:58,550
Please, have a seat.

134
00:09:58,884 --> 00:10:03,740
Sorry, it’s a bit messy in here.

135
00:10:03,764 --> 00:10:07,774
Something happened last week,
so we still haven’t cleaned up.

136
00:10:08,769 --> 00:10:11,896
It’s okay. Our editorial office
is even messier than this.

137
00:10:13,789 --> 00:10:18,043
By the way, our Editor-in-Chief
is an avid fan of your blog.

138
00:10:18,415 --> 00:10:19,587
Really?

139
00:10:19,611 --> 00:10:22,872
It started when I heard Q.E.D.
had case blogs.

140
00:10:22,896 --> 00:10:24,642
I read your blogs right away.

141
00:10:24,666 --> 00:10:27,196
And I must say,
you have a talent for writing.

142
00:10:28,086 --> 00:10:30,505
Oh, wow, thank you so much! I mean…

143
00:10:30,507 --> 00:10:33,844
that’s a huge compliment
coming from an editor like yourself.

144
00:10:34,511 --> 00:10:39,951
And, you know, the Clarion releases
a literary folio quarterly.

145
00:10:39,975 --> 00:10:45,146
So we get short stories, poems,
and essays from students,

146
00:10:45,147 --> 00:10:47,399
even non-Clarion members.

147
00:10:47,733 --> 00:10:51,359
And I’m here to formally let you know

148
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:54,906
that our EIC wants to feature
some of your works.

149
00:10:55,327 --> 00:10:56,619
What? Really?

150
00:10:56,620 --> 00:10:59,748
Yes, because I believe
you have a knack for storytelling.

151
00:11:01,205 --> 00:11:03,165
Thank you. Thank you so much.

152
00:11:03,172 --> 00:11:05,161
And don’t worry.

153
00:11:05,185 --> 00:11:08,522
If there’s any payment
for the pieces you submit,

154
00:11:08,529 --> 00:11:10,629
the Clarion is willing to make a deal.

155
00:11:11,448 --> 00:11:13,241
Our EIC really wants it,

156
00:11:13,242 --> 00:11:16,870
so we’ll do everything we can
to make it happen.

157
00:11:16,894 --> 00:11:19,288
Well, there's really no need to pay me.

158
00:11:19,289 --> 00:11:24,739
It means a lot that my blog posts
might make it into your folio, so...

159
00:11:25,194 --> 00:11:26,236
That’s great!

160
00:11:26,587 --> 00:11:30,507
But would it be okay if your articles
go through the editing process?

161
00:11:30,843 --> 00:11:34,847
You know,
print space is kind of limited.

162
00:11:35,222 --> 00:11:37,724
As long as the flow of the story
stays the same

163
00:11:37,725 --> 00:11:40,017
and no important details are lost,

164
00:11:40,018 --> 00:11:41,895
I’m fine with it.

165
00:11:42,344 --> 00:11:43,845
Okay! Okay! Okay! Thank you!

166
00:11:44,162 --> 00:11:46,039
Our EIC will definitely be happy.

167
00:11:46,911 --> 00:11:47,912
Oh, right!

168
00:11:48,562 --> 00:11:52,670
- By the way, this is my card.
- Oh, perfect.

169
00:11:53,084 --> 00:11:55,461
Sorry, I don’t have a card yet.

170
00:11:55,462 --> 00:11:59,063
It’s okay. Just message me there
if there are any updates.

171
00:11:59,087 --> 00:12:00,088
Okay.

172
00:12:03,043 --> 00:12:05,683
By the way,
how’s your president doing?

173
00:12:06,139 --> 00:12:10,477
Word got to us that
he was poisoned.

174
00:12:11,311 --> 00:12:13,748
Well, he’s still recovering.

175
00:12:13,772 --> 00:12:17,191
The doctor advised him
to rest for now,

176
00:12:17,192 --> 00:12:18,905
so he won’t be able
to come in yet.

177
00:12:19,637 --> 00:12:23,701
The belladonna he drank
might still be affecting his system.

178
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:26,787
Belladonna, huh.

179
00:12:27,512 --> 00:12:29,639
Yeah. Why?

180
00:12:29,663 --> 00:12:33,708
Do you also write about
the cases here on campus?

181
00:12:34,490 --> 00:12:37,826
Actually, we really want to publish
a series of articles

182
00:12:37,827 --> 00:12:40,097
regarding these gruesome incidents.

183
00:12:40,121 --> 00:12:42,205
But the admin won’t allow it.

184
00:12:42,206 --> 00:12:46,461
They said it’s bad
for the school’s "image."

185
00:12:46,971 --> 00:12:51,225
And they said it might affect
the students’ mental health

186
00:12:51,226 --> 00:12:55,110
if we publish something,
you know, depressing.

187
00:12:55,117 --> 00:12:56,994
I see. I understand.

188
00:12:57,986 --> 00:13:02,199
Actually,
I wanted to bring a case to you.

189
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:04,618
Since I’m already here,

190
00:13:04,623 --> 00:13:07,209
I thought I’d bring it up too,
if that’s okay.

191
00:13:07,223 --> 00:13:09,642
Of course. What is it?

192
00:13:16,416 --> 00:13:19,544
He’s Edward Allen Ponce.

193
00:13:20,101 --> 00:13:22,854
He’s one of our contributors
for the literary section.

194
00:13:23,526 --> 00:13:28,489
He loves writing stories,
specifically mystery stories.

195
00:13:29,127 --> 00:13:33,214
Yesterday, he was found dead
in his apartment.

196
00:13:34,975 --> 00:13:35,975
Murder?

197
00:13:39,094 --> 00:13:42,221
A bottle of potassium cyanide
capsules was found

198
00:13:42,222 --> 00:13:45,392
on the nearby table
where he was found dead.

199
00:13:47,644 --> 00:13:51,857
His breath smelled like almonds,
and his lips had turned blue

200
00:13:52,316 --> 00:13:57,988
They also found a note on the table,
so they ruled it self-inflicted.

201
00:14:01,436 --> 00:14:05,231
If that’s the police’s conclusion,
what’s bothering you?

202
00:14:05,692 --> 00:14:09,696
His farewell note
was weirdly written.

203
00:14:10,135 --> 00:14:14,439
I’ve edited enough of his stories
to know his writing style,

204
00:14:14,463 --> 00:14:18,424
and as far as I can tell,
there’s something off about it.

205
00:14:19,128 --> 00:14:21,767
This written confession isn’t a hoax.

206
00:14:22,890 --> 00:14:25,726
Suicide will redeem my guilt as killer.

207
00:14:26,908 --> 00:14:31,704
Forgive me, Nicole, for I took
without remorse that writer’s life.

208
00:14:32,523 --> 00:14:34,123
Manuscipt is Unbeknownst

209
00:14:34,130 --> 00:14:36,459
which I’ve stolen reveals truth.

210
00:14:37,418 --> 00:14:39,336
Keep the copy as evidence.

211
00:14:39,350 --> 00:14:41,436
Is this his handwriting?

212
00:14:42,395 --> 00:14:47,525
Based on the note and his notebooks,
the handwriting matches.

213
00:14:48,234 --> 00:14:50,027
But you’re right, Agatha.

214
00:14:50,028 --> 00:14:52,391
There really is something weird
with this note.

215
00:14:53,114 --> 00:14:56,700
Yes, and if the police are right,

216
00:14:56,701 --> 00:15:01,456
Edward killed a writer
and stole their manuscript.

217
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:13,259
"Unbeknownst" was the working title,
just like what’s written there.

218
00:15:14,594 --> 00:15:15,720
I see.

219
00:15:16,846 --> 00:15:20,558
Wait, who’s Nicole,
and who’s the writer he allegedly killed?

220
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:23,227
Nicole was Edward’s girlfriend.

221
00:15:23,519 --> 00:15:26,759
But we still don’t know
which writer they’re referring to.

222
00:15:27,523 --> 00:15:29,720
Maybe it was someone they knew,
or a friend of theirs.

223
00:15:31,564 --> 00:15:33,099
Could you forward this to me?

224
00:15:41,537 --> 00:15:43,884
The police ruled it self-inflicted,

225
00:15:44,415 --> 00:15:47,363
but according to the client,
and based on my deduction

226
00:15:47,961 --> 00:15:50,241
there’s something off
about the subject’s final note.

227
00:15:50,768 --> 00:15:51,784
What do you think?

228
00:15:55,405 --> 00:15:56,656
Excuse me for a moment.

229
00:15:58,346 --> 00:15:59,490
Hello?

230
00:15:59,514 --> 00:16:00,807
It’s too easy.

231
00:16:01,182 --> 00:16:02,183
Too easy!

232
00:16:02,665 --> 00:16:05,548
One look is all it takes
for me to solve the puzzle.

233
00:16:06,976 --> 00:16:10,332
The victim did not take his own life,
but was forced to.

234
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:12,120
Again?

235
00:16:12,455 --> 00:16:17,098
So if this is like all the other cases,
then that means it’s connected to…

236
00:16:17,122 --> 00:16:19,020
If you’re thinking
that Moriarty is involved,

237
00:16:20,202 --> 00:16:21,536
I highly doubt it.

238
00:16:22,474 --> 00:16:23,641
So what is it?

239
00:16:23,642 --> 00:16:26,235
Can you stop with the
suspense and just tell me

240
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:28,159
what really happened to Edward?

241
00:16:28,751 --> 00:16:29,919
Hmm…

242
00:16:30,734 --> 00:16:31,897
Nope!

243
00:16:31,921 --> 00:16:33,089
What do you mean, “nope”?

244
00:16:33,403 --> 00:16:34,529
I'm not telling you.

245
00:16:34,927 --> 00:16:36,011
Why would I?

246
00:16:36,651 --> 00:16:40,675
In the first place, you let our landlady
lock me inside of this unit

247
00:16:40,678 --> 00:16:42,347
and you didn’t even
bother to help me.

248
00:16:42,372 --> 00:16:43,456
Secondly...

249
00:16:43,481 --> 00:16:46,150
you can handle this case
even without my help.

250
00:16:47,171 --> 00:16:49,422
We’ve been working
together for weeks.

251
00:16:49,423 --> 00:16:52,260
Surely you’ve picked up
some of my methods by now.

252
00:16:52,789 --> 00:16:54,848
I’m confident that
you can solve this case

253
00:16:55,746 --> 00:16:56,974
on behalf of our club.

254
00:17:01,169 --> 00:17:02,337
Why aren’t you answering?

255
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:06,692
Have you lost your voice
or have you fainted from the pressure?

256
00:17:06,696 --> 00:17:09,438
My God! Can you just tell me already?

257
00:17:09,463 --> 00:17:10,463
I’m feeling pressured.

258
00:17:10,468 --> 00:17:13,866
What if I can’t solve this case
and embarrass our club?

259
00:17:15,101 --> 00:17:17,228
And our client’s from The Clarion.

260
00:17:17,687 --> 00:17:20,081
I’m scared I’ll disappoint her

261
00:17:20,087 --> 00:17:22,464
because I’m not as good
as she expects me to be.

262
00:17:23,012 --> 00:17:24,013
Still no.

263
00:17:24,525 --> 00:17:27,737
But let me give you a clue
before you start cracking the case.

264
00:17:28,065 --> 00:17:29,732
Have you ever taken an exam

265
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:32,027
where you're one seat apart
from your classmate?

266
00:17:33,824 --> 00:17:34,825
Yes.

267
00:17:35,698 --> 00:17:37,074
What’s that supposed to mean?

268
00:17:37,784 --> 00:17:38,784
Good luck!

269
00:17:38,785 --> 00:17:40,017
Huh? Wait!

270
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:48,783
What kind of clue is that?

271
00:17:51,817 --> 00:17:54,027
Agatha, I need your help.

272
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:57,694
Do you think Nicole will come?

273
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:01,615
She said yes to your text,
so I guess we just wait.

274
00:18:04,829 --> 00:18:07,206
Oh, here. She’s here. Nicole.

275
00:18:07,231 --> 00:18:11,213
Hello! Nicole, meet Lorelei.
Lorelei, meet Nicole.

276
00:18:11,238 --> 00:18:12,574
- Hi!
- Hi! Nice to meet you!

277
00:18:12,585 --> 00:18:14,211
How can I help you?

278
00:18:14,898 --> 00:18:17,388
Actually, I’m from the Q.E.D. Club.

279
00:18:17,391 --> 00:18:21,436
I just wanted to ask you a few things
about Edward Allen.

280
00:18:22,451 --> 00:18:24,537
Is this about his death?

281
00:18:28,885 --> 00:18:31,930
We have a hunch he didn’t kill himself.

282
00:18:32,573 --> 00:18:34,700
Well, not voluntarily.

283
00:18:36,017 --> 00:18:40,563
So you’re saying someone
forced him to take cyanide?

284
00:18:41,265 --> 00:18:42,529
It looks that way.

285
00:18:42,553 --> 00:18:45,556
That’s why we were
hoping for your help

286
00:18:45,580 --> 00:18:50,252
to find out what really happened
and who might’ve done it.

287
00:18:51,336 --> 00:18:55,319
In the note, he mentioned a writer
he supposedly killed

288
00:18:55,343 --> 00:18:57,303
and stole a manuscript from.

289
00:18:58,176 --> 00:19:01,179
Do you know
who he was referring to?

290
00:19:02,868 --> 00:19:05,246
Maybe Arthur Dominguez.

291
00:19:05,726 --> 00:19:07,060
Like Ed...

292
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:10,355
Art was a mystery writer too.

293
00:19:10,939 --> 00:19:13,734
But two weeks ago,
he hit his head.

294
00:19:13,998 --> 00:19:15,994
They said he accidentally fell
down the stairs

295
00:19:16,018 --> 00:19:18,437
at the dorm where he
and Ed were together.

296
00:19:19,592 --> 00:19:25,014
Do you also know about the manuscript
Edward mentioned in the note?

297
00:19:28,406 --> 00:19:32,494
All he told me when we
were still together was that,

298
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:35,692
he was writing a novel

299
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:37,801
he planned to submit
to a publishing house.

300
00:19:38,344 --> 00:19:41,492
Writing? Are you kidding?

301
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,765
Maybe what you mean is,

302
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:48,771
he was revising the manuscript
he stole to make it his own.

303
00:19:49,462 --> 00:19:50,463
Isn’t that right?

304
00:19:50,657 --> 00:19:53,668
If he wasn’t stealing
Arthur’s actual writing,

305
00:19:53,692 --> 00:19:56,173
he was stealing his ideas.

306
00:19:56,197 --> 00:19:59,615
A lot of Clarion pieces
were credited to Edward,

307
00:19:59,619 --> 00:20:02,414
but Art was the one
who actually wrote them.

308
00:20:03,399 --> 00:20:05,558
Good thing his conscience
finally got to him.

309
00:20:05,583 --> 00:20:09,129
Honestly, that’s still not enough
for everything he’s done.

310
00:20:16,052 --> 00:20:17,721
Please excuse him.

311
00:20:18,555 --> 00:20:20,807
Michael and Art were best friends.

312
00:20:21,630 --> 00:20:27,719
And Michael strongly suspects Edward
had something to do with Art’s accident.

313
00:20:28,903 --> 00:20:31,364
Alright, I should get going too.
I still have class.

314
00:20:31,791 --> 00:20:34,210
Can I contact you directly?

315
00:20:34,681 --> 00:20:37,600
In case there are updates on the case.

316
00:20:38,709 --> 00:20:39,710
Sure.

317
00:20:42,125 --> 00:20:44,377
- Here. Thank you.
- Thank you.

318
00:20:47,659 --> 00:20:49,744
- Agatha…
- Yes, Lori?

319
00:20:49,769 --> 00:20:50,924
I have a strong hunch

320
00:20:50,925 --> 00:20:53,928
Michael had something to do
with Edward’s death.

321
00:20:55,984 --> 00:20:57,068
You think so?

322
00:20:57,932 --> 00:21:02,312
For now, he’s the only one I can see
with a motive to do it.

323
00:21:04,189 --> 00:21:08,777
I’ll follow him and find out the truth.

324
00:21:17,911 --> 00:21:21,623
How do I figure out the
hidden message in this note?

325
00:21:23,273 --> 00:21:24,691
Good afternoon, class.

326
00:21:25,225 --> 00:21:27,536
We will have a surprise exam for today.

327
00:21:28,006 --> 00:21:31,801
I just want to see what you’ve learned
from what I taught you last session.

328
00:21:33,986 --> 00:21:38,532
Oh? What are you so worried about?
We've discussed the topic already.

329
00:21:38,937 --> 00:21:40,563
And this is history class.

330
00:21:40,564 --> 00:21:45,110
You know you have to learn from the past
in order to face the future, right?

331
00:21:45,444 --> 00:21:50,657
So, go get your papers
and move your chairs away from each other.

332
00:21:50,682 --> 00:21:53,393
The space between you
should be one seat apart.

333
00:21:57,508 --> 00:21:59,221
Have you ever taken an exam

334
00:21:59,252 --> 00:22:01,495
where you're one seat apart
from your classmate?

335
00:22:01,519 --> 00:22:04,166
The space between you
should be one seat apart.

336
00:22:09,283 --> 00:22:10,743
One seat apart!

337
00:22:11,363 --> 00:22:12,405
That’s it!

338
00:22:30,701 --> 00:22:33,204
Lorelei! Did you decode Edward’s note?

339
00:22:33,577 --> 00:22:34,577
Yes.

340
00:22:35,269 --> 00:22:38,292
But I want us to wait for Nicole first.

341
00:22:38,316 --> 00:22:41,528
I want her to hear
what her boyfriend was trying to say.

342
00:22:50,508 --> 00:22:52,718
Why did you call me back, Lorelei?

343
00:22:53,171 --> 00:22:56,132
Do you have an update
on Edward’s case?

344
00:22:56,157 --> 00:22:57,158
Yes!

345
00:22:57,742 --> 00:23:00,055
I have decoded your boyfriend’s note.

346
00:23:00,079 --> 00:23:04,091
So you can stop pretending now
and just turn yourself in.

347
00:23:06,251 --> 00:23:07,669
Wait, what do you mean?

348
00:23:08,041 --> 00:23:10,752
Nicole is responsible
for Edward’s death?

349
00:23:11,639 --> 00:23:13,869
Since Edward loved mysteries,

350
00:23:13,893 --> 00:23:17,607
I realized that was his plan all along,

351
00:23:17,631 --> 00:23:21,224
to hide the message in his poem.

352
00:23:22,043 --> 00:23:26,405
Whoever forced him to drink the poison
was definitely keeping watch.

353
00:23:30,381 --> 00:23:33,170
I tried taking out
some of the words here.

354
00:23:33,194 --> 00:23:37,082
I tried different combinations,
but this one fit best.

355
00:23:38,616 --> 00:23:40,493
Exactly two words apart.

356
00:23:40,926 --> 00:23:45,046
If you take out the two words
between each keyword,

357
00:23:45,060 --> 00:23:46,687
that’s what it reads.

358
00:23:47,688 --> 00:23:50,273
"This isn't suicide.

359
00:23:50,274 --> 00:23:57,239
My killer, Nicole, took that manuscript
which reveals the evidence."

360
00:23:58,515 --> 00:24:03,191
I only did it to avenge Art
for what Ed did to him.

361
00:24:04,095 --> 00:24:05,096
What?

362
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:07,274
How could you do that
to your boyfriend?

363
00:24:07,968 --> 00:24:09,136
The truth is...

364
00:24:10,210 --> 00:24:12,045
Art and I grew up together.

365
00:24:16,008 --> 00:24:19,360
Looks like our friend’s feeling down.
You okay?

366
00:24:19,384 --> 00:24:21,764
Hey, Art. Are you okay?

367
00:24:21,788 --> 00:24:24,305
That story is mine! I’m sure of it!

368
00:24:24,329 --> 00:24:28,750
But Ed, he submitted it to the Clarion
and said he wrote it.

369
00:24:29,379 --> 00:24:32,345
If you wrote this,
how does he have a copy?

370
00:24:32,358 --> 00:24:35,211
I don’t know. We were roommates.

371
00:24:35,242 --> 00:24:39,037
So maybe he was sneaking into my room
and checking my notebook,

372
00:24:39,061 --> 00:24:41,935
where I wrote all my stories.

373
00:24:42,547 --> 00:24:44,466
Have you talked to him about it?

374
00:24:44,490 --> 00:24:46,878
Yeah! But he kept denying it!

375
00:24:46,902 --> 00:24:50,381
He said maybe it was just a coincidence
that we had the same idea.

376
00:24:50,405 --> 00:24:53,282
That wasn’t even the first time.
It happened several times before.

377
00:24:53,283 --> 00:24:54,660
Then that guy’s a total jerk.

378
00:24:54,684 --> 00:24:57,079
Want to punch him when we see him?

379
00:24:57,103 --> 00:24:59,915
No. You’ll just end up
looking like the bad guy.

380
00:25:02,084 --> 00:25:03,418
I’ve got an idea.

381
00:25:04,993 --> 00:25:09,759
Since not many people know
the three of us are friends,

382
00:25:11,571 --> 00:25:13,657
what if I flirt with Ed?

383
00:25:14,531 --> 00:25:15,782
Right?

384
00:25:15,806 --> 00:25:21,066
Then once he falls for me,
I’ll make him confess to what he did.

385
00:25:21,090 --> 00:25:25,386
Once we have the evidence,
that’s when we expose everything.

386
00:25:26,247 --> 00:25:27,374
That’ll work.

387
00:25:27,415 --> 00:25:29,793
- Right? How about you?
- That's nice.

388
00:25:31,127 --> 00:25:32,337
Sounds good.

389
00:25:33,087 --> 00:25:37,109
I already got Ed to confess
to plagiarizing your work.

390
00:25:37,133 --> 00:25:40,803
I have his confession on my phone.
Listen to this.

391
00:25:41,512 --> 00:25:43,723
My roommate was such an idiot.

392
00:25:44,181 --> 00:25:46,517
He writes his stories in his notebook.

393
00:25:46,944 --> 00:25:48,946
And he just leaves it
lying around the room.

394
00:25:50,102 --> 00:25:54,000
Of course, I’d take photos of it,
then just revise it myself.

395
00:25:54,024 --> 00:25:55,442
To make it look like it was mine.

396
00:25:56,026 --> 00:25:58,946
Babe, why did you do that?

397
00:25:59,512 --> 00:26:01,305
So I could be the star, of course!

398
00:26:01,699 --> 00:26:03,770
Art didn’t deserve
to be famous anyway.

399
00:26:04,399 --> 00:26:07,110
It just hits different
when your name’s in the Clarion.

400
00:26:07,536 --> 00:26:08,871
He’s such a loser.

401
00:26:10,457 --> 00:26:14,508
I also got the photos of your stories
from his phone.

402
00:26:14,532 --> 00:26:15,825
There! Look!

403
00:26:16,113 --> 00:26:18,174
So, do we leak it?

404
00:26:18,186 --> 00:26:20,968
No! I’ll confront him myself!

405
00:26:21,601 --> 00:26:23,141
Next thing we knew,

406
00:26:23,165 --> 00:26:25,835
Art had already hit his head
in their dorm.

407
00:26:26,492 --> 00:26:29,704
We had no proof Edward did it,

408
00:26:30,672 --> 00:26:36,136
so there was nothing we could do
when he made it look like an accident.

409
00:26:37,762 --> 00:26:39,597
I can’t take it anymore!

410
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:43,143
I can’t stand what he did to Art.

411
00:26:44,269 --> 00:26:46,020
He’s my childhood friend.

412
00:26:46,688 --> 00:26:48,940
I know what a good person he is.

413
00:26:49,596 --> 00:26:53,933
So I took matters into my own hands
to avenge him.

414
00:26:54,540 --> 00:26:58,117
Of course, I’d take pictures of it,
then just revise it myself.

415
00:26:58,569 --> 00:27:00,218
To make it look like it was mine.

416
00:27:00,242 --> 00:27:05,582
I’ll release this recording
if you don’t do what I say.

417
00:27:06,667 --> 00:27:09,461
I know you can’t
handle the shame, Ed.

418
00:27:10,296 --> 00:27:11,648
Please don’t.

419
00:27:11,672 --> 00:27:15,718
Let’s talk this out, Nicole.
Nicole, please? Nicole.

420
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:18,448
What’s your dad gonna say
when he finds out

421
00:27:18,472 --> 00:27:20,806
- about the shameful things you’re doing?
- Please.

422
00:27:21,733 --> 00:27:23,578
We can talk this through.

423
00:27:23,602 --> 00:27:26,146
- Isn’t he running for councilor?
- Nicole.

424
00:27:26,171 --> 00:27:30,091
What happens when people find out
his son’s a plagiarist?

425
00:27:32,002 --> 00:27:36,298
What you need to do now
is write your goodbye note.

426
00:27:36,323 --> 00:27:37,658
Don’t. Please?

427
00:27:37,683 --> 00:27:38,809
Write!

428
00:27:39,659 --> 00:27:40,827
Write!

429
00:27:53,579 --> 00:27:55,539
How could you do that to Art?

430
00:27:56,296 --> 00:27:59,299
He was such a good person,
and you did that to him?

431
00:27:59,847 --> 00:28:03,100
You know what should happen to you?
You should disappear.

432
00:28:04,541 --> 00:28:05,792
Drink this.

433
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:08,769
Drink it!

434
00:28:09,790 --> 00:28:10,999
Please.

435
00:28:24,006 --> 00:28:26,133
I was consumed by anger.

436
00:28:27,586 --> 00:28:32,758
The only thing on my mind
was avenging Art.

437
00:28:33,290 --> 00:28:37,377
Because I can’t accept that this is
all that would happen to him.

438
00:28:37,759 --> 00:28:40,938
Art was too kind and innocent

439
00:28:40,962 --> 00:28:43,297
to be treated like that by anyone.

440
00:28:44,694 --> 00:28:47,697
Nicole! You shouldn’t have done that!

441
00:28:48,228 --> 00:28:50,606
You should’ve let the police handle it!

442
00:28:51,101 --> 00:28:52,811
I’m sorry...

443
00:28:54,234 --> 00:28:55,903
I’m sorry.

444
00:28:55,906 --> 00:28:59,362
- Sorry, forgive me. What's this?
- There! Arrest her!

445
00:28:59,364 --> 00:29:01,908
- What's this? Wait!
- Arrest her.

446
00:29:01,909 --> 00:29:03,910
- Come with us.
- I don't want.

447
00:29:03,911 --> 00:29:07,663
- Wait! Michael!
- Come. Let's go outside.

448
00:29:07,664 --> 00:29:11,376
- Michael!
- Thank you. Leave her to us.

449
00:29:13,045 --> 00:29:15,255
Thank you so much for your help, Lorelei.

450
00:29:16,325 --> 00:29:21,038
I’m so lucky I got to personally witness
how Q.E.D. solves cases.

451
00:29:21,813 --> 00:29:23,064
No problem.

452
00:29:29,706 --> 00:29:30,791
Loki!

453
00:29:32,951 --> 00:29:35,370
Hey. I brought you food.

454
00:29:38,528 --> 00:29:39,529
Thank you.

455
00:29:39,905 --> 00:29:43,991
So, aren’t you proud of me
for solving my first case on my own?

456
00:29:45,953 --> 00:29:47,663
Technically, I still helped you.

457
00:29:48,538 --> 00:29:50,540
I gave you a clue, right?

458
00:29:50,794 --> 00:29:54,214
So, you still weren’t on your own?

459
00:29:55,045 --> 00:29:56,630
Just eat already.

460
00:29:57,005 --> 00:29:59,174
Let me finish fixing
this blog post first.

461
00:30:08,558 --> 00:30:09,559
Oh, no!

462
00:30:10,185 --> 00:30:11,895
The account’s suspended.

463
00:30:13,872 --> 00:30:15,499
What could’ve happened?

464
00:30:17,192 --> 00:30:19,569
It means a lot of people
reported the account.

465
00:30:20,529 --> 00:30:22,614
Just appeal and wait for 30 days.

466
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:24,865
You haven't violated anything

467
00:30:24,866 --> 00:30:27,869
so I'm pretty confident
that they'll lift the suspension.

468
00:30:29,329 --> 00:30:30,329
For now...

469
00:30:31,408 --> 00:30:33,952
I want you to write it
in a secured drive.

470
00:30:47,363 --> 00:30:51,325
Are you sure you’re really okay, Loki?
Can you handle it?

471
00:30:52,267 --> 00:30:53,267
Yep.

472
00:30:54,016 --> 00:30:55,309
Never been better.

473
00:30:55,687 --> 00:30:56,688
Good.

474
00:30:57,105 --> 00:30:59,392
Because there’s something
I want to discuss

475
00:30:59,417 --> 00:31:02,497
that I couldn’t bring up
while you were recovering.

476
00:31:03,102 --> 00:31:04,186
What is it?

477
00:31:06,544 --> 00:31:11,942
Do you remember when John Bautista
almost had me dissolved?

478
00:31:14,037 --> 00:31:17,874
When I heard him call
and talk to Moriarty.

479
00:31:19,093 --> 00:31:21,439
When he called that number,

480
00:31:21,463 --> 00:31:26,676
I heard it play familiar children's tune.

481
00:31:27,761 --> 00:31:31,222
And that song
was "Mary Had a Little Lamb."

482
00:31:33,850 --> 00:31:35,352
"Mary Had a Little Lamb"?

483
00:31:37,265 --> 00:31:38,485
Are you sure?

484
00:31:38,492 --> 00:31:39,825
A hundred percent sure.

485
00:31:40,411 --> 00:31:43,664
Well, I won’t be surprised
if that were true.

486
00:31:44,986 --> 00:31:48,198
Moriarty’s probably fond
of nursery rhymes.

487
00:31:49,653 --> 00:31:52,656
First, "Twinkle Twinkle Little Star."

488
00:31:53,246 --> 00:31:55,791
Now, "Mary Had A Little Lamb."

489
00:31:56,328 --> 00:31:59,164
What’s next?
"London Bridge is Falling Down"?

490
00:31:59,764 --> 00:32:02,016
That’s pretty much the same thing, Loki.

491
00:32:02,955 --> 00:32:05,791
Anyway, going back to my story.

492
00:32:06,825 --> 00:32:11,747
While you were in the hospital,
I heard a man whistling.

493
00:32:12,427 --> 00:32:13,887
It was the same tune.

494
00:32:24,069 --> 00:32:26,202
When I confronted him,

495
00:32:26,210 --> 00:32:29,593
he said he only heard it
from someone's keypad

496
00:32:29,607 --> 00:32:32,110
at the hospital
around that time too.

497
00:32:34,545 --> 00:32:35,922
Do I know you, miss?

498
00:32:36,698 --> 00:32:42,736
So I'm sure one of Moriarty's men
was at the hospital.

499
00:32:43,169 --> 00:32:45,148
Loki, this could be the key

500
00:32:45,172 --> 00:32:47,894
for us to really find out
who Moriarty really is.

501
00:32:48,592 --> 00:32:51,345
You should have told me
about this keypad thingy sooner.

502
00:32:52,304 --> 00:32:54,930
I would’ve been able to focus
my undivided attention

503
00:32:54,931 --> 00:32:57,100
on figuring out what the digits are.

504
00:32:58,791 --> 00:32:59,959
Even if we know the tune,

505
00:33:01,278 --> 00:33:05,901
the list of the possible
number configurations is endless.

506
00:33:05,925 --> 00:33:09,012
It could've been one of
your visitors who dialed it.

507
00:33:10,042 --> 00:33:12,471
First, was Professor Morayta.

508
00:33:13,576 --> 00:33:15,578
Then, Bastien Montreal.

509
00:33:16,398 --> 00:33:20,819
And lastly, your brother, Luthor.

510
00:33:22,988 --> 00:33:24,114
But, wait.

511
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:27,172
There's another possibility.

512
00:33:28,452 --> 00:33:33,123
That night, a man with a lollipop
was following me.

513
00:33:34,235 --> 00:33:35,528
I don't know him.

514
00:33:36,335 --> 00:33:37,961
I don't know his name.

515
00:33:38,269 --> 00:33:42,169
But if I saw his face,
I'd definitely recognize him.

516
00:33:42,762 --> 00:33:47,058
Whoever it was, we need to be careful
about the people approaching us.

517
00:33:49,223 --> 00:33:51,725
We don't know what
Moriarty's planning.

518
00:33:53,548 --> 00:33:58,588
All we can do for now
is practice constant vigilance.

519
00:33:59,108 --> 00:34:02,128
So don’t forget to bring
your stun pen at all times.

520
00:34:02,152 --> 00:34:06,406
We'll never know
when he or his minions will strike.

521
00:34:11,650 --> 00:34:14,986
Hi. Sorry, am I disturbing you?

522
00:34:14,987 --> 00:34:16,613
We are in the middle
of something important.

523
00:34:16,614 --> 00:34:19,634
- Can you please stop--
- Rosetta, come in.

524
00:34:19,658 --> 00:34:22,830
I'm with the friend I told you about.

525
00:34:23,412 --> 00:34:25,664
Sure. That's fine. Please, come in.

526
00:34:26,415 --> 00:34:27,415
Come on.

527
00:35:02,883 --> 00:35:03,883
Hi.

528
00:35:06,766 --> 00:35:08,309
Rhea?

529
00:35:15,378 --> 00:35:20,994
Is he okay?
Why does he seem to be buffering?

530
00:35:21,992 --> 00:35:25,706
Sorry, what was your friend's
name again?

531
00:35:25,710 --> 00:35:28,477
My name’s Jamie Santiago.
Pleased to meet you.

532
00:35:28,483 --> 00:35:30,798
Nice to meet you. I'm Lorelei Rios.

533
00:35:30,799 --> 00:35:33,965
And this is our club president,
Loki Mendez.

534
00:35:35,550 --> 00:35:39,709
Jamie is one of the best
theater actresses in school.

535
00:35:39,733 --> 00:35:42,406
That's why she always
gets the lead roles.

536
00:35:42,411 --> 00:35:46,198
She's popular on campus,
but maybe you don't know her

537
00:35:46,198 --> 00:35:49,951
since you don't watch our theater plays.

538
00:35:55,179 --> 00:35:57,013
Alright, I'll go ahead.

539
00:35:57,014 --> 00:36:00,643
Lori, please help out my friend, okay?
Thank you.

540
00:36:00,668 --> 00:36:01,794
We got this.

541
00:36:02,901 --> 00:36:03,902
Bye.

542
00:36:04,482 --> 00:36:07,999
Jamie, please feel free
to tell us your problem.

543
00:36:08,024 --> 00:36:10,585
We’re here to listen. Right, Loki?

544
00:36:12,128 --> 00:36:16,049
Earlier, Rosie said I'm a theater actress.

545
00:36:16,643 --> 00:36:20,595
I'm used to meeting fans
after every production I lead.

546
00:36:20,610 --> 00:36:22,320
It's never really been an issue.

547
00:36:23,496 --> 00:36:26,833
What scares me are the
ones hiding in the dark

548
00:36:27,375 --> 00:36:29,287
and staying anonymous.

549
00:36:29,301 --> 00:36:31,688
You mean stalkers?

550
00:36:31,694 --> 00:36:34,627
Yeah. I once chatted with someone.

551
00:36:34,651 --> 00:36:40,323
The name wasn’t familiar,
and it looked like a fake account.

552
00:36:40,991 --> 00:36:44,831
At first,
he was even trying to befriend me.

553
00:36:44,855 --> 00:36:46,098
Then in the following days,

554
00:36:46,122 --> 00:36:49,751
he suddenly started sending
photos of me while I was onstage.

555
00:36:50,335 --> 00:36:54,130
I want to know who he is
because I want him to stop.

556
00:36:54,589 --> 00:36:57,268
Do you have copies of the photos
you were talking about?

557
00:37:02,971 --> 00:37:03,971
Loki.

558
00:37:04,889 --> 00:37:05,889
Hey!

559
00:37:07,403 --> 00:37:09,603
When did these photos start?

560
00:37:10,269 --> 00:37:11,492
Last week.

561
00:37:11,523 --> 00:37:14,944
The first one was sent Tuesday
at 7:56 in the evening.

562
00:37:15,653 --> 00:37:18,614
Then the next one
was sent Wednesday at 8:34.

563
00:37:20,184 --> 00:37:23,700
And the latest one
was last night at 9:45.

564
00:37:24,270 --> 00:37:27,245
Are these from your rehearsals
for the play at the auditorium?

565
00:37:29,721 --> 00:37:31,138
More likely than not,

566
00:37:31,139 --> 00:37:34,327
that’s one of your
Repertory Club members.

567
00:37:34,351 --> 00:37:37,145
Based on the angles in these photos.

568
00:37:38,131 --> 00:37:39,799
Why is he doing this?

569
00:37:40,732 --> 00:37:44,152
Well, maybe he likes you.

570
00:37:44,903 --> 00:37:50,951
He’s too shy to tell you how he feels,
so he’s doing it through chat instead.

571
00:37:51,365 --> 00:37:53,158
It’s starting to get creepy.

572
00:37:53,183 --> 00:37:56,644
I want to make him stop,
but I don’t know who to confront.

573
00:37:57,228 --> 00:38:00,231
That kind of behavior from a fan
is definitely worrying.

574
00:38:00,482 --> 00:38:04,944
So you need to be extra careful,
especially when you're alone.

575
00:38:05,779 --> 00:38:08,615
We’ll be needing your chat records
with the mystery guy.

576
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:15,955
We need to understand the culprit first
before we gather our suspects.

577
00:38:16,731 --> 00:38:19,775
We’ll also ask
for a list of all your club members.

578
00:38:20,930 --> 00:38:25,184
Then we narrow it down
to the possible suspects.

579
00:38:25,518 --> 00:38:27,727
We don’t have an official member list,

580
00:38:27,728 --> 00:38:31,023
but I remember the names
of all 42 members.

581
00:38:31,043 --> 00:38:32,544
I’ll just write them down.

582
00:38:33,269 --> 00:38:36,313
You memorized all 42 members’ names?

583
00:38:36,323 --> 00:38:40,469
Yes! With full names and ages.

584
00:38:40,493 --> 00:38:42,244
I have a very retentive memory,

585
00:38:42,245 --> 00:38:45,582
so memorizing my lines for a play
has never been hard for me.

586
00:38:46,291 --> 00:38:49,127
I can remember things quickly.

587
00:38:51,087 --> 00:38:54,382
I’ll just write it down
and send it right away.

588
00:39:04,893 --> 00:39:07,771
Why do you seem so
starstruck by Jamie?

589
00:39:08,944 --> 00:39:09,944
Hey!

590
00:39:10,315 --> 00:39:13,360
I've been talking to you,
and you're not even answering me.

591
00:39:15,494 --> 00:39:16,787
Wait, what’s that?

592
00:39:20,367 --> 00:39:23,327
I thought you were doing
something important.

593
00:39:23,328 --> 00:39:25,021
You were just browsing.

594
00:39:27,290 --> 00:39:30,368
This is relevant to our case.
Just so you know.

595
00:39:30,910 --> 00:39:35,164
I’m just checking the profiles
of everyone on Jamie’s list.

596
00:39:35,789 --> 00:39:38,041
I’m reading and studying
how they construct

597
00:39:38,042 --> 00:39:42,379
their self-centered,
if not utterly ridiculous, Facenote posts.

598
00:39:43,547 --> 00:39:46,759
It’s giving me headache,
but I have to do it.

599
00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:49,887
How is that connected to our case?

600
00:39:53,057 --> 00:39:54,849
You don’t know
that you can recognize someone

601
00:39:54,850 --> 00:39:56,435
through their writer’s fist?

602
00:39:56,810 --> 00:39:58,312
Not your literal fist.

603
00:39:58,979 --> 00:40:00,272
But the way you write.

604
00:40:00,773 --> 00:40:03,691
You can identify them
with their word choice

605
00:40:03,692 --> 00:40:05,277
and sentence construction.

606
00:40:08,697 --> 00:40:10,699
Check this Mister Y’s message to Jamie.

607
00:40:11,700 --> 00:40:15,538
I noticed that you have good curves.
Do you work out everyday?

608
00:40:16,426 --> 00:40:18,887
I saw you wearing
strawberry lipstick today.

609
00:40:19,625 --> 00:40:22,586
I can’t help but wonder
how those lips taste like.

610
00:40:23,254 --> 00:40:27,049
Can I touch your legs?
I guess they’re freaking smooth.

611
00:40:27,522 --> 00:40:28,522
Creepy.

612
00:40:29,607 --> 00:40:30,608
Definitely.

613
00:40:31,609 --> 00:40:37,031
And most of all, a very lame alias.

614
00:40:37,935 --> 00:40:39,728
If we don’t stop this,

615
00:40:40,605 --> 00:40:42,231
it could turn into an obsession,

616
00:40:42,256 --> 00:40:44,133
and he might do something worse to Jamie.

617
00:40:44,634 --> 00:40:46,135
So this is what we're gonna do.

618
00:40:46,427 --> 00:40:49,222
Let's divide the list
that Jamie sent to us.

619
00:40:49,514 --> 00:40:53,017
And we will both check
the profiles of these people.

620
00:40:53,226 --> 00:40:56,270
I'll do the first 21,
and you take the next.

621
00:40:56,979 --> 00:40:59,565
Then let's meet up later
with our findings.

622
00:41:00,816 --> 00:41:01,816
Got it.

623
00:41:02,951 --> 00:41:03,951
Good.

624
00:41:08,374 --> 00:41:13,421
Okay, class, remember,
you make your own grades.

625
00:41:14,128 --> 00:41:18,507
So just submit what we discussed, okay?

626
00:41:18,966 --> 00:41:20,217
Okay, class.

627
00:41:20,770 --> 00:41:24,482
Don’t forget the outputs that you have
to submit by the end of the month.

628
00:41:25,176 --> 00:41:28,387
Remember, you're young adults now,
so be responsible.

629
00:41:28,722 --> 00:41:30,682
Your grades are up to you, okay?

630
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:36,869
And if you have any concerns,
just come to me. I'm easy to talk to.

631
00:41:37,369 --> 00:41:38,369
But then again...

632
00:41:39,426 --> 00:41:44,627
And, remember, your performance tasks
must be done on time.

633
00:41:44,632 --> 00:41:48,011
So if there are no more concerns,
class dismissed!

634
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:50,703
Wesley Nuñez.

635
00:41:52,021 --> 00:41:53,439
Raymond Torres.

636
00:41:55,597 --> 00:41:57,057
Alvin Mendoza.

637
00:41:58,052 --> 00:42:01,681
And Stein Alberts.

638
00:42:03,261 --> 00:42:05,429
Stein Alberts? The name is familiar.

639
00:42:06,352 --> 00:42:07,395
Who is he again?

640
00:42:07,854 --> 00:42:09,456
The math prodigy.

641
00:42:09,480 --> 00:42:11,733
The one we saved in one of our cases.

642
00:42:13,818 --> 00:42:15,028
I remember now.

643
00:42:15,396 --> 00:42:19,334
But I can’t believe
he’s a possible suspect.

644
00:42:19,365 --> 00:42:21,576
So what are you
gonna do with that list?

645
00:42:24,178 --> 00:42:26,138
We will be observing them firsthand.

646
00:42:27,557 --> 00:42:29,225
And we have to see them in person

647
00:42:29,642 --> 00:42:32,353
and know more about
what they've done in the production.

648
00:42:33,020 --> 00:42:37,775
Then, we’ll lay out a trap
that can expose him.

649
00:42:38,734 --> 00:42:41,445
And how exactly
are you planning on doing that?

650
00:42:41,904 --> 00:42:43,072
Don’t worry.

651
00:42:44,448 --> 00:42:45,700
I have something in mind.

652
00:42:53,541 --> 00:42:55,585
Can we attend your
rehearsal by tomorrow?

653
00:43:01,882 --> 00:43:02,967
Sure!

654
00:43:09,932 --> 00:43:12,077
Come on, we're gonna be late
for our next class!

655
00:43:12,107 --> 00:43:13,267
Exactly, what time is it now?

656
00:43:14,353 --> 00:43:15,353
Just a moment.

657
00:43:15,354 --> 00:43:17,607
Only ten minutes left,
we're gonna be late.

658
00:43:23,738 --> 00:43:25,424
Lori!

659
00:43:25,448 --> 00:43:26,699
- Jamie.
- Hi!

660
00:43:27,575 --> 00:43:28,826
Where’s Loki?

661
00:43:29,827 --> 00:43:32,955
He’ll be here soon.
He’s always on time anyway.

662
00:43:33,414 --> 00:43:35,166
We’re just early.

663
00:43:42,673 --> 00:43:43,673
Lori…

664
00:43:45,551 --> 00:43:46,886
can I ask something?

665
00:43:47,970 --> 00:43:49,055
What is it?

666
00:43:53,601 --> 00:43:56,854
Is there something going on
between you and Loki?

667
00:43:57,229 --> 00:43:58,230
What?

668
00:43:58,689 --> 00:44:00,125
Nothing.

669
00:44:00,149 --> 00:44:02,985
Loki and I are just clubmates,
and roommates.

670
00:44:03,319 --> 00:44:06,822
Besides, I can’t imagine myself
falling for that guy.

671
00:44:10,627 --> 00:44:12,254
Just as I thought.

672
00:44:12,903 --> 00:44:15,864
Loki will never fall
for someone like you.

673
00:44:17,071 --> 00:44:18,113
I was actually wondering

674
00:44:18,114 --> 00:44:21,201
why you’re always trailing
behind him like a puppy.

675
00:44:21,225 --> 00:44:26,098
And why do you think Loki accepted
your club application?

676
00:44:26,122 --> 00:44:31,877
You look like a dumb chihuahua
with no talents and art of detection.

677
00:44:33,933 --> 00:44:37,228
Face card?
It’s pretty unremarkable.

678
00:44:38,020 --> 00:44:42,692
Or was it because you bribed him
to let you join?

679
00:44:46,621 --> 00:44:47,705
I'm here.

680
00:44:48,072 --> 00:44:50,157
Finally, Loki, you’re here!

681
00:44:53,536 --> 00:44:54,662
Are you okay?

682
00:44:57,248 --> 00:44:59,584
Yeah, of course.

683
00:45:12,421 --> 00:45:14,673
- We're here!
- Wait.

684
00:45:18,259 --> 00:45:21,248
- Oh, my God, Jamie!
- Hi!

685
00:45:21,253 --> 00:45:24,397
I'm Stein Alberts.
And I'm pleased to meet the two of you.

686
00:45:24,410 --> 00:45:26,579
What's a Math major
like yourself doing here?

687
00:45:27,779 --> 00:45:30,846
Shouldn't you be solving
complex mathematical equations?

688
00:45:30,866 --> 00:45:34,869
As a director,
it's my job to ensure the audience

689
00:45:34,870 --> 00:45:36,210
gets a high-quality viewing experience.

690
00:45:36,234 --> 00:45:37,861
I'll help you, okay?

691
00:45:38,558 --> 00:45:40,113
You'll get better.

692
00:45:46,544 --> 00:45:51,465
So now that we've met her four suspects,
who do you think is our mystery guy?
